---
description: Refactor patterns: split files, keep public API stable, no behavior change
globs: src/**/*.{ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: false
---

## Refactor rules (no behavior change)

- Keep behavior identical. Refactors must be structural only (file moves/splits, renames, deduplication) and should not change runtime results or UI output.
- Preserve existing public APIs (especially `index.ts` barrels). When splitting, keep imports for callers stable.
- Follow FSD import rules: only import through slice `index.ts` public API (no deep imports).

## Preferred patterns used in this repo

### 1) Facade + internal modules (shared/api)

- When a file grows large, split into focused modules (types/errors/utils/request) but keep a small facade that re-exports the prior surface.
- Example structure:
  - `shared/api/api-client.ts` (facade exports)
  - `shared/api/{cookies,types,errors,request}.ts` (implementation details)

### 2) Widget UI decomposition (widgets/app-layout)

- Keep container components responsible for state + derived data.
- Extract pure presentational parts into colocated subcomponents under the widget.
- Example:
  - `widgets/app-layout/ui/Sidebar.tsx` (state + filtering)
  - `widgets/app-layout/ui/sidebar/*` (item/search/sections)

### 3) Derived lookup helpers at module scope (navigation)

- Avoid repeating `flatMap/find` in render paths.
- Prefer a module-scope `Map` lookup in the same slice:
  - `widgets/app-layout/model/nav-lookup.ts` exports `getNavTitle(pathname)`

### 4) Split config/types/icons for readability

- Keep types in a dedicated file (e.g. `nav-types.ts`).
- Keep ReactNode icon constants separated (e.g. `nav-icons.tsx`).
- Keep config data (`navGroups`) readable.

## Verification

- After refactors, run `npm run lint` and `npm run build`.

